frameDefinitions: This frame contains nouns denoting Quantities of a specified Entity and their numerical Values.
An event or state (here termed an Eventuality) or time-Period is described in terms of the Degree to which its duration diverges from a standard.
The size of an Entity is assessed in terms of the Degree by which it deviates from the norm.
An Agent suddenly and often violently separates the Whole_patient into two or more smaller Pieces, resulting in the Whole_patient no longer existing as such.
An Entity has a particular scalar Attribute with a value exceeding a contextually-specified or generally-understood standard.
This frame concerns  words that express an Object's position on a scale, its Measurement, with respect to some attribute, its Dimension.
frameExamples: His heart attack was caused by a high cholesterol <t>level</t>.
After a <t>lengthy</t> discussion with the Foreign Minister, Mr. Qian Qichen, they met the Prime Minister.
He <t>ripped</t> <t>up</t> the letter faster than you can say 'Jack Robbins'. INI
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Entity</fen> identifies the concept or substance being quantified by a <fen>Quantity</fen>.
<fen>Value</fen> identifies the numerical amount of the <fen>Entity</fen>.

A situation, action or event whose duration is being described.  The Eventuality occurs as the External Argument if the adjective is used predicatively, or as the modified noun if the adjective is used attributively: <fex name='Eventuality'>The lecture</fex> was <t>short</t>. We had a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Eventuality'>conversation</fex>.

Sometimes these adjectives describe simply a period of time, rather than an event or state.  The Period almost invariably occurs as the modified noun with an attributive adjective: We waited for only a <t>short</t> <fex name='Period'>time</fex>. Use of the drug over a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Period'>period</fex> can cause memory loss.
The thing whose size is being considered.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional action that results in the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> being broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The entity which is destroyed by the <fen>Agent</fen> and that ends up broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The fragments of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> that result from the <fen>Agent</fen>'s action.
An event which leads to the fragmentation of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks up the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> into pieces.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Value</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Value</fen> for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Dimension</fen> which is measured.  Most LUs in this frame incorporate the <fen>Dimension</fen>.
<fen>Object</fen> identifies the item which is measured along one of its <fen>Dimension</fen>s.
<fen>Measurement</fen> identifies the extent of the <fen>Object</fen> along the specified <fen>Dimension</fen>.
listRoleExamples: Their <fex><t>level</t></fex> of productivity decreased with each hour of overtime worked.
He wrote me a check in the amount <fex>of $500</fex>.
<fex>I and I alone</fex> can shatter the gem and break the curse.
Shattering someone's confidence is a little different than shattering <fex>a dish</fex>.
I smashed the toy boat <fex>to flinders</fex>.
The  new vase is 5 cm in circumference at the top.
<fex>The  new vase</fex> is 5 cm in circumference at the top.
The  new vase is <fex>5 cm</fex> in circumference at the top.
